# The local e2e/regtest environment is now provided by the `regtest` git
# submodule (arkade-regtest) and driven by its Node CLI (`regtest.mjs`). There is
# no longer a Go-source arkd checkout to configure here.
#
# arkd's image and configuration (exit delays, intent fees, …) live in
# `.env.regtest`, which is passed to the stack via `just regtest-start`
# (`node regtest/regtest.mjs start --env .env.regtest`). Edit that file to tune
# arkd; you generally do not need a `.env` at all.
#
# Quick start:
#   git submodule update --init --recursive    # or: just regtest-init
#   just regtest-start                          # bring up the stack
#   just e2e-tests                              # run the e2e suite
#   just regtest-clean                          # tear it down
